WhiteListModel v 0.1 Beta
==============

Instead of use white_list_helper in every view just use it as model before_filter!

== Requirements

white_list (http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/white_list/)

== Usage

class News < ActiveRecord::Base
  white_list   # Filter all string or text fields with standard white_list_helper
end

class News < ActiveRecord::Base
  white_list :only => [ :description ]  # Filter description field with standard white_list_helper
end

== Avalible parameters

:only => []       # Filter only included fields
:except => []     # Filter all string or text fields except included
:tags => []       # Add specified tags to allowed list
:attributes => [] # Add specified attributes to allowed list

== Other informations

This plugin for now uses white_list_helper class so any modyfications within base tags/attributes of WhiteListHelper class will change behawior of this plugin.

